f say 20, if you multiclass (lets say fighter/thief for example) then you only get to level 10 in each class.  To me that seems weaker than having a figher that is level 20 or a thief that is level 20.  Am I right in this line of thinking?  Also it has always been my thought that dual classes are the same way.  You stop playing a Mage some time before 10, then start all over again as lets say a theif.  Once you reach the level you had when you were a mage, you gain your mage abilities.  Yet again, xp total is still capped so you will never obtain level 20 in either class.<br><br>Since I have always felt this way I always roll up either a Ranger/Paladin, or a pure class (mage/thief/fighter/priest).  Anyone want to provide their thoughts on this topic, and explain to me why people play multiclass characters?<br><br>Thanks!<br><br>-Uladar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/ugladimir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gladimir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puny Skeleton</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/27/02 2:16:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=206.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.san.rr.com/vagabondia/images/brain60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question of opinion on class/multiclass/dual class choic</span><hr size=1> I think people multi/dual class for utility or just plain enjoyment.  A Rogue with a little wizard abilities on the side can be quite nice.  A fighter with some of the Rogue's stealth skills can be quite beneficial.  There is the ever popular Ranger/Cleric that makes a nice addition to a party, and my old pen and paper buddies always has a Cleric/Wizard in the group whenever possible.<br><br>Even if the character is only 10/10, that does not mean they can't still be very useful.  Remember the Tomb of Horrors module?  IIRC, a few of the wandering monster encounters for that module were things like 10-60 orcs, 5-20 Bugbears, etc.  This is acceptable because random/wandering encounters are generally designed to &quot;wear down&quot; the party by causing the characters to use up spells, potions, wand charges, etc.<br><br>Even when fighting the big nasty demi-lich at the end, a level 10/10 Cleric-Wizard would be pretty useful.  If nothing else, they Raise Dead!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>- gladimir@san.rr.com<BR><a href=http://camelot.vagabondia.net/>Gladimir's Camelot Site</a><BR><a href=http://www.vagabondia.net/>Vagabondia Online - June 2002</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/usegalsoulsaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Segal SoulSaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=112539253&img=5" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lead-GM</span><br>  Posts: 2688<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/27/02 6:38:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=206.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question of opinion on class/multiclass/dual class choic</span><hr size=1> I agree that a 20th level single class is stronger than a 10/10 dual class but you have to remember that this are Pen and Paper rules which means...<br><br>1) The imbalance only appears at higher levels, a 7/3 Fighter/Cleric is probably much more powerful than a 10 Fighter or a 10 Cleric.<br><br>2) In Pen and Paper, it takes years to get to level 20.  Having played 1st edition most my life, I have never seen a 20th level character. <p><b>Segal SoulSaver</b><br>Lead DM - <a href="http://Shroudworld.com">Shroud World</a> <BR>A NWN Persistent Campaign<BR><i>And so it was that the gods gifted upon mortal men the varied treasures and mankind was changed for the better and worse, but forever changed. </i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/uscorchbrimstone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scorch Brimstone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kobold Runt</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/1/02 10:40:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=206.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question of opinion on class/multiclass/dual class choic</span><hr size=1> good post, help me out alot<br><br><br><br><br><br>Modred Blackmarra-----Apex<br><br>Nivius Nightbird---------Tried and True<br><br>Scorch Brimstone---------Hansum shamun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>If yooz can't dazzle dem with brillyance, yooz bash dem gud... har har ..abd umm yooz ummm bash dem sum more. Rar !Har har har..............</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/uamberyllarydunmorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amberyll Arydunmorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1154<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/1/02 2:15:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=206.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <